AttributeList.Text: This block is for monitoring and adjusting the total and current running hours, and time until next inspection.
This network resets the MaintenanceRequired bit every scan.

This network allows the running hours to be adjusted from the HMI.
When the Save bit is set to TRUE from the HMI, Depending on Which other bits have been toggled by the HMI, the AdjustedHours are moved into the Hours bits. Or they are reset to 0.
The Oneshot, is used so that the Save button cannot be held on resulting on the Hours constantly being set to 0.

This network calculates the total Lifetime hours.
If Running = TRUE, everytime SecondsPulse = TRUE, 1 second is added to the TotalSeconds count. SecondsPulse is being triggered at a frequency of 1HZ.
TotalSeconds is always being divided by 60, to find the Total Minutes.
When the TotalMinutes = 60, 1 is added to the TotalHours count, and the TotalSeconds are reset to 0.

This network calculates the Current Running Hours.
If Running = TRUE, everytime SecondsPulse = TRUE, 1 second is added to the CurrentSeconds count. SecondsPulse is being triggered at a frequency of 1HZ.
CurrentSeconds is always being divided by 60, to find the Total Minutes.
When the CurrentMinutes = 60, 1 is added to the CurrentHours count, and the CurrentSeconds are reset to 0.

This network calculates the remaining time until maintenance by subtracting the current running hours from the maintenance period. It also calculates the remaining minutes until maintenance by subtracting the current minutes from the hour.
If the Current Minutes = 0, then the CurrentHours is subtracted from the MaintenancePeriod, the result is moved into the HoursUntilMaintenance and 0 is moved into the MinutesUntilMaintenance. If the CurrentsHours >= MaintenanceAlarmTime, then the MainteanceRequired bit is set to TRUE.
If the Current Minutes >= 1, then the CurrentHours is Subtracted from the MaintenancePeriod and the result is moved into the HoursUntilMaintenanceTemp. Which then has 1 subtracted from it, and the result moved into HoursUntilMaintenance. The CurrentMinutes are subtracted from 60, and the result moved into the MinutesUntilMaintenance. If the CurrentsHours >= MaintenanceAlarmTime, then the MainteanceRequired bit is set to TRUE.
